WEBVTT

00:02.268 --> 00:03.269
Amanda: PREVIOUSLY ON "THE HAVES
AND THE HAVE NOTS"...

00:03.269 --> 00:04.470
Jeffery:
I HAD SEX WITH THE GIRL.

00:04.470 --> 00:06.072
JEFFERY, DO YOU THINK
THIS MAKES YOU STRAIGHT NOW?

00:06.072 --> 00:07.207
NO.

00:07.207 --> 00:08.374
MY NAME'S QUINCY.

00:08.374 --> 00:09.743
YOU KNOW A GIRL
NAMED CANDACE?

00:09.743 --> 00:10.744
DOES SHE KNOW YOU?

00:10.744 --> 00:11.845
I'M HER BABY'S FATHER.

00:11.845 --> 00:13.079
TURN YOURSELF IN.

00:13.079 --> 00:14.948
ALL I HAVE TO DO
IS COP TO THE WARRANTS I HAVE?

00:14.948 --> 00:15.982
AND ONE MORE.

00:15.982 --> 00:18.284
Candace:
SOMEBODY TOOK A LOT FROM ME ‐‐

00:18.284 --> 00:19.620
EVERYTHING, BASICALLY.

00:19.620 --> 00:20.954
YOU WANT US
TO TAKE CARE OF HIM?

00:20.954 --> 00:23.456
I WANT HIM BROUGHT HERE
SO I CAN HANDLE HIM MYSELF.

00:23.456 --> 00:26.259
HOLD ON A SECOND.
LET ME EXPLAIN.

00:32.633 --> 00:34.300
MOM.

00:36.870 --> 00:38.404
JEFFERY.

00:46.680 --> 00:48.915
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

00:53.620 --> 00:55.355
WE WERE JUST TALKING.

00:55.355 --> 00:57.490
I WAS TALKING TO MY SON!

01:00.493 --> 01:04.237
NOW, ANSWER ME, BOY.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

01:08.374 --> 01:09.543
I ‐‐ I WAS ‐‐ I WAS ‐‐

01:09.543 --> 01:13.013
I ASKED JEFFERY
TO MEET ME HERE.

01:13.013 --> 01:15.516
YOU ASKED HIM
TO MEET YOU?

01:15.516 --> 01:17.283
YES.
WHY?

01:20.854 --> 01:22.989
I NEEDED TO
TALK TO MY SON.

01:22.989 --> 01:24.490
ABOUT WHAT?

01:26.159 --> 01:29.896
VERONICA,
CAN WE TALK IN PRIVATE?

01:29.896 --> 01:35.368
NOT UNTIL YOU TELL ME WHY
OUR SON IS HERE WITH HIM.

01:35.368 --> 01:37.838
WITH HIM, YOU MEAN WHAT?

01:37.838 --> 01:39.405
WHO ARE YOU, BOY?

01:39.405 --> 01:41.742
I AM VERY CLEAR ABOUT WHAT ‐‐
UH, LANDON, LANDON, NO, NO ‐‐

01:41.742 --> 01:44.044
NO, JEFFERY, JEFFERY,
LET HIM.

01:45.378 --> 01:48.114
NOW, WHAT WERE YOU GOING TO SAY?

01:50.751 --> 01:53.019
HMM?

02:00.894 --> 02:03.837
VERONICA,
CAN WE TALK IN MY ROOM?

02:03.837 --> 02:05.338
I DON'T HAVE A DAMN THING TO SAY
TO YOU.

02:05.338 --> 02:09.009
VERONICA, YOU WILL CALM DOWN,
AND WE WILL TALK.

02:09.009 --> 02:11.778
NO, WE WON'T.
DOWNSTAIRS, JEFFERY.

02:11.778 --> 02:13.346
NOW.

02:16.750 --> 02:19.385
DAVID, I AM SO SORRY.

02:19.385 --> 02:22.756
LOOK,
IT'S ‐‐ IT'S FINE.

02:22.756 --> 02:24.691
SEE YOU AT
THE CAMPAIGN HEADQUARTERS.

02:26.026 --> 02:27.393
OKAY.

02:28.762 --> 02:32.899
UH, DAD,
WHAT'S GOING ON?

02:32.899 --> 02:37.403
SON, MEET ME IN MY OFFICE
AT THE CAMPAIGN HEADQUARTERS.

02:39.372 --> 02:42.475
JEFFERY...

02:42.475 --> 02:45.111
IT'S OKAY.

02:45.111 --> 02:48.448
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

02:48.448 --> 02:50.551
OKAY.

02:52.653 --> 02:54.621
MR. HARRINGTON.

02:54.621 --> 02:56.657
LANDON.

03:00.026 --> 03:02.368
SHOULD WE HOLD THE ELEVATOR
FOR YOU?

03:02.368 --> 03:05.171
NO.
I'LL CATCH THE NEXT ONE.

03:07.874 --> 03:09.242
OKAY.

03:16.617 --> 03:19.620
‐‐Captions by VITAC‐‐
www.vitac.com

03:19.620 --> 03:22.656
CAPTIONS PAID FOR BY
DISCOVERY COMMUNICATIONS

03:36.336 --> 03:37.671
HOW LONG?
TWO MINUTES.

03:37.671 --> 03:39.506
COMING RIGHT UP, MA'AM.
YOU HAVE ONE.

03:42.743 --> 03:44.410
ARE WE RIDING TOGETHER,
MAGGIE?

03:44.410 --> 03:46.146
[ CLEARS THROAT ] YES.

03:46.146 --> 03:47.648
CAN I GET A CAB, PLEASE?

03:47.648 --> 03:49.182
SURE, RIGHT AWAY.

03:49.182 --> 03:51.417
JEFFERY,
YOU WILL RIDE WITH ME.

03:53.720 --> 03:55.889
WE'RE GOING
IN DIFFERENT DIRECTIONS.

03:55.889 --> 03:57.891
I'LL SAY.

03:57.891 --> 04:00.360
Landon:
WE HAVE ROOM, JEFFERY.

04:00.360 --> 04:02.302
IT'S AN S. U. V.,
AND WE'RE GOING TO THE OFFICE.

04:02.302 --> 04:06.006
I SAID
HE WOULD RIDE WITH ME.

04:06.006 --> 04:07.674
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT,
JEFFERY?

04:07.674 --> 04:11.311
WHY WAS MY SON
IN YOUR ROOM?

04:11.311 --> 04:12.813
YOU SHOULD TALK TO YOUR SON.

04:12.813 --> 04:16.416
I WILL,
HENCE THE RIDE TOGETHER.

04:16.416 --> 04:18.519
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT,
JEFFERY?

04:18.519 --> 04:21.287
AGAIN, I SAY,
"WHO ARE YOU, BOY?"

04:21.287 --> 04:23.790
MY NAME IS LANDON.

04:23.790 --> 04:26.159
DO YOU NOT REMEMBER
MEETING ME?

04:26.159 --> 04:28.895
OF COURSE.
I REMEMBER YOU.

04:28.895 --> 04:32.065
PERHAPS YOU HAVEN'T
BEEN EDUCATED ON WHO I AM.

04:32.065 --> 04:33.166
MRS. HARRINGTON,
THIS IS REALLY ‐‐

04:33.166 --> 04:34.668
I WASN'T SPEAKING TO YOU.

04:34.668 --> 04:36.402
I WAS JUST GOING TO SAY ‐‐
NOTHING.

04:38.905 --> 04:43.143
BECAUSE I WASN'T
SPEAKING TO YOU.

04:45.846 --> 04:48.682
NOW, LET'S MAKE THIS
AN EASY MOMENT FOR BOTH OF US

04:48.682 --> 04:50.784
BECAUSE WE ARE IN PUBLIC,

04:50.784 --> 04:53.286
BUT I'M ABOUT TWO INCHES
OFF YOUR ASS,

04:53.286 --> 04:55.021
SO IF I WERE YOU,
I WOULD GO OVER THERE

04:55.021 --> 04:56.790
AND SHUT UP
WHILE I TALK TO THIS CHILD.

04:56.790 --> 04:59.025
NOW, I DON'T KNOW
WHO YOU THINK YOU ARE,

04:59.025 --> 05:01.061
BOTH OF YOU,
ROLLING INTO THIS TOWN,

05:01.061 --> 05:05.005
INTO MY TOWN,
PLAYING THESE GROWN‐UP GAMES,

05:05.005 --> 05:07.440
BUT YOU HAD BETTER ‐‐

05:07.440 --> 05:11.177
YOU BOTH
HAD BETTER THINK TWICE.

05:12.412 --> 05:14.848
YES, MA'AM.

05:14.848 --> 05:16.750
I'LL TALK TO YOU LATER,
JEFFERY.

05:16.750 --> 05:17.851
YEAH, OKAY.

05:17.851 --> 05:19.720
NO, YOU WON'T.

05:26.627 --> 05:28.595
Landon: THANK YOU, SIR.

05:31.798 --> 05:33.499
Man:
HOW YOU DOING, BUDDY?

05:36.402 --> 05:38.438
[ CAR DOOR SHUTS ]

05:44.945 --> 05:46.947
DON'T YOU MOVE.

05:50.250 --> 05:52.953
WHY DID THEY GET THEIR CAR
BEFORE ME?

05:54.287 --> 05:56.289
Man: THEY CALLED DOWN.
I‐IT'S ON THE WAY UP.

05:56.289 --> 05:57.624
I TOLD YOU
TO LEAVE IT OUT.

05:57.624 --> 05:59.826
I'M ALWAYS HERE.
THEY ALWAYS LEAVE IT OUT.

05:59.826 --> 06:01.535
ARE YOU NEW?

06:01.535 --> 06:03.403
S‐SORRY, MA'AM.

06:14.014 --> 06:17.217
SHE IS SUCH A BITCH.
WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT ABOUT?

06:17.217 --> 06:20.286
[ SCOFFS ] I WAS JUST ABOUT TO
ASK YOU THE SAME THING.

06:20.286 --> 06:22.188
WHAT?

06:22.188 --> 06:24.958
WHAT WAS HE DOING
IN YOUR ROOM?

06:27.160 --> 06:28.595
HIS DAD CALLED FOR HIM.

06:29.630 --> 06:31.064
LANDON, CUT THE CRAP.

06:31.064 --> 06:32.298
WHAT?

06:32.298 --> 06:33.700
WHAT IS GOING ON?

06:33.700 --> 06:35.536
NOTHING.

06:42.843 --> 06:44.244
WHAT IS GOING ON?

06:44.244 --> 06:45.879
I SAID NOTHING.
LET IT GO.

06:45.879 --> 06:47.047
NO.

06:47.047 --> 06:48.348
I'M NOT SAYING ANYTHING.

06:49.315 --> 06:50.951
[ SCOFFS ]

06:52.018 --> 06:53.353
SO, HE'S GAY.

06:54.487 --> 06:56.757
HERE ARE THE REPORTS
YOU ASKED FOR.

06:56.757 --> 06:58.625
THE DATA SHOWS THAT
IT IS A GOOD DAY

06:58.625 --> 07:00.426
TO ANNOUNCE
JUDGE CRYER'S RUNNING,

07:00.426 --> 07:04.170
BARRING ANY UNFORESEEN DISASTERS
IN THE NEWS.

07:04.170 --> 07:06.840
OKAY, FINE,
DON'T TELL ME.

07:06.840 --> 07:08.441
I WILL FIND OUT.

07:08.441 --> 07:10.577
YOU ALWAYS DO, DARLING.

07:12.278 --> 07:13.747
HMM.

07:14.781 --> 07:17.450
YES. I DO.

07:19.653 --> 07:21.154
HMM.

07:31.264 --> 07:33.166
HEY.

07:38.605 --> 07:40.473
[ CRIES ]

07:40.473 --> 07:41.808
LET ME GO.

07:41.808 --> 07:43.043
NO.

07:43.043 --> 07:44.110
LET ME GO.

07:44.110 --> 07:47.848
SWEETHEART,
I'M NOT LETTING GO OF YOU.

07:49.215 --> 07:50.884
JEFFERY,
LET'S GET IN THE CAR.

07:50.884 --> 07:52.385
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

07:52.385 --> 07:54.387
I'M GOING FOR A RIDE
WITH MY SON.

07:54.387 --> 07:56.222
NO, HE'S RIDING WITH ME.

07:56.222 --> 07:58.224
HE WILL RIDE WITH ME.

07:58.224 --> 08:01.067
JEFFERY,
DON'T GET IN THAT CAR.

08:01.067 --> 08:03.970
HE WILL RIDE WITH ME, DAVID.

08:03.970 --> 08:06.573
I SAID,
DON'T GET INTO THAT CAR.

08:06.573 --> 08:08.474
I CALLED FOR MY CAR.
WHERE IS IT?

08:08.474 --> 08:10.310
Man: YES, MR. HARRINGTON,
IT'S COMING RIGHT UP.

08:10.310 --> 08:11.778
THANK YOU.

08:13.313 --> 08:14.615
I'M JUST GONNA RIDE
WITH MOM.

08:14.615 --> 08:16.617
NO, YOU'RE NOT.
DAD.

08:16.617 --> 08:17.818
NO, YOU ARE NOT.

08:17.818 --> 08:19.485
I DON'T WANT YOU GUYS
ARGUING ABOUT ME.

08:19.485 --> 08:22.122
JEFFERY, YOU WILL RIDE WITH ME,
AND THAT SETTLES IT.

08:26.326 --> 08:29.029
SO, YOU'RE NOT
GETTING IN THE CAR, JEFFERY?

08:29.029 --> 08:30.531
NO, HE'S NOT.

08:30.531 --> 08:32.265
WHERE'S HIS CAR?

08:32.265 --> 08:34.701
SON,
YOU'RE HOLDING UP TRAFFIC.

08:34.701 --> 08:38.772
SON, YOU DON'T HAVE TO
BE AFRAID OF HER.

08:41.241 --> 08:43.343
YES, I DO.

08:43.343 --> 08:45.211
SON.

08:45.211 --> 08:47.914
I'M GONNA RIDE WITH HER,
DAD.

08:49.249 --> 08:50.483
I'M SORRY.

08:54.220 --> 08:56.189
DON'T BE AFRAID.

08:57.290 --> 08:58.324
[ CAR DOOR SHUTS ]

09:43.043 --> 09:44.645
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

09:52.452 --> 09:54.655
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

10:04.805 --> 10:06.840
CAN I HELP YOU?

10:06.840 --> 10:08.575
I'M LOOKING
FOR JUDGE CRYER.

10:08.575 --> 10:10.210
WHOM SHALL I SAY
IS CALLING?

10:10.210 --> 10:11.244
DETECTIVE MARSHALL.

10:11.244 --> 10:12.946
SURE.

10:19.385 --> 10:21.588
IT'S FOR YOUR OWN GOOD,
SWEETHEART. IT IS.

10:21.588 --> 10:23.557
FINE, FINE.
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

10:23.557 --> 10:24.625
CELINE.

10:24.625 --> 10:26.660
EXCUSE ME,
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

10:26.660 --> 10:28.762
YES, EVERYTHING IS FINE.

10:28.762 --> 10:30.997
GIVE US SOME PRIVACY,
WOULD YOU?

10:30.997 --> 10:32.866
OH, THERE'S SOMEONE HERE
TO SEE YOU.

10:32.866 --> 10:34.568
WHO?
DETECTIVE MARSHALL.

10:36.336 --> 10:38.338
OH, ALL RIGHT.

10:44.711 --> 10:46.580
GOOD MORNING, AMANDA.

10:46.580 --> 10:48.682
WHAT'S SO GOOD ABOUT IT?

10:48.682 --> 10:49.983
YOU'RE ALIVE.

10:49.983 --> 10:51.852
IS THAT A GOOD THING?

10:51.852 --> 10:53.987
YES, IT IS.

10:55.421 --> 10:57.390
HEY, CELINE, WHOSE POLICE CAR
IS DOWNSTAIRS?

10:57.390 --> 10:59.693
OH, THERE'S NO POLICE CAR
DOWNSTAIRS.

10:59.693 --> 11:01.768
YEAH, THERE IS.

11:01.768 --> 11:05.271
OH, OH, THAT'S
DETECTIVE MARSHALL'S CAR.

11:06.439 --> 11:08.709
WHAT DOES HE WANT?
YOUR DAD.

11:08.709 --> 11:10.143
YOU KNOW WHAT FOR?

11:10.143 --> 11:11.612
NOPE, I SURE DON'T.

11:11.612 --> 11:14.347
WHAT'S, UH, GOING ON?

11:16.282 --> 11:18.985
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

11:18.985 --> 11:21.421
I'M REALLY GLAD
YOU'RE HOME.

11:21.421 --> 11:23.489
THANKS.

11:23.489 --> 11:25.959
WHERE WERE YOU?

11:25.959 --> 11:27.060
YOU DON'T KNOW?

11:27.060 --> 11:28.294
NO.

11:29.329 --> 11:31.231
I WAS IN JAIL, AMANDA.

11:31.231 --> 11:33.634
I KNEW THAT.

11:33.634 --> 11:36.002
THEN WHY DID YOU
SAY YOU DIDN'T?

11:36.002 --> 11:38.071
[ SIGHS ]
STOP TALKING TO ME!

11:39.906 --> 11:42.643
WOW.
WHAT IS GOING ON WITH HER?

11:42.643 --> 11:44.511
YOU KNOW MY SISTER.

11:44.511 --> 11:47.581
YES,
BUT SHE SEEMS TO BE WORSE.

11:47.581 --> 11:50.817
CAN YOU FIND OUT WHAT
THE DETECTIVE WANTS, PLEASE?

11:50.817 --> 11:54.821
WYATT,
YOU KNOW I DON'T SNOOP.

11:54.821 --> 11:56.456
CELINE.

11:56.456 --> 11:57.791
WHAT?

11:57.791 --> 11:59.993
YOU KNOW EVERYTHING
THAT GOES ON IN THIS HOUSE.

11:59.993 --> 12:03.403
AY, MIJO, NOT LATELY.

12:22.155 --> 12:24.525
WAIT, HOLD UP, MAN.
HOW MUCH IS THIS CAB?

12:24.525 --> 12:26.059
BENNY.
WHAT?

12:26.059 --> 12:27.728
WELL, HE'S CHARGING US
TOO MUCH.

12:27.728 --> 12:29.663
IT'S LIKE FOUR MILES
FROM THE HOSPITAL.

12:29.663 --> 12:32.599
WHAT IS IT, LIKE ‐‐
THAT'S $5 ‐‐ THAT'S $5 A MILE.

12:32.599 --> 12:34.167
THANK YOU, SIR.

12:34.167 --> 12:36.837
[ LAUGHS ] MAN.

12:36.837 --> 12:38.972
[ SCOFFS ]

12:44.077 --> 12:46.246
[ DOG BARKS ]

12:46.246 --> 12:48.114
WOULD YOU STOP
BEING SO GROUCHY?

12:48.114 --> 12:50.283
I'M NOT BEING GROUCHY.
I JUST KNOW WE NEED THE MONEY.

12:50.283 --> 12:53.620
NO, IT'S FINE. LISTEN,
DON'T WORRY ABOUT THE MONEY.

12:53.620 --> 12:54.955
GOD WILL MAKE A WAY.

12:54.955 --> 12:56.089
UGH, HERE YOU GO.

12:56.089 --> 12:58.158
OH, DON'T START NOW,
BENJAMIN.

12:58.158 --> 13:00.126
I JUST KNOW
WE NEED THE MONEY.

13:00.126 --> 13:01.902
[ SMACKS LIPS ]
IT'S FINE, BENNY.

13:01.902 --> 13:04.170
DON'T WORRY
ABOUT THE MONEY.

13:05.972 --> 13:09.009
GOD WILL ALWAYS
MAKE A WAY.

13:09.009 --> 13:10.911
OH, AND HERE WE GO
WITH THAT.

13:10.911 --> 13:12.513
SEE,
DON'T START WITH ME, NOW.

13:12.513 --> 13:14.280
WHAT, ARE YOU ABOUT TO BRING
THE HOLY ROLLER OUT NOW?

13:14.280 --> 13:15.582
YES, I AM. UH‐HUH.
YOU KEEP IT UP,

13:15.582 --> 13:17.618
AND I'M GONNA EMBARRASS YOU
IN FRONT OF ALL THESE PEOPLE!

13:17.618 --> 13:19.419
[ LAUGHS ]
MM‐HMM.

13:22.889 --> 13:25.058
WAIT, WHOA, WHOA.

13:26.560 --> 13:28.795
WHO CUT MY GRASS?

13:28.795 --> 13:30.096
MICHAEL.

13:30.096 --> 13:32.465
WHAT'S A MICHAEL?

13:32.465 --> 13:34.801
HE'S A MAN WHOSE GRANDDAUGHTER
WAS HIT.

13:34.801 --> 13:37.237
HE WAS LONELY
AND NEEDED SOMETHING TO DO,

13:37.237 --> 13:39.105
SO HE CAME
AND CUT THE GRASS.

13:39.105 --> 13:40.406
OH, REALLY?

13:40.406 --> 13:42.042
YEAH.

13:42.042 --> 13:43.376
WHY YOU ASKING ME
LIKE THAT?

13:43.376 --> 13:45.512
BECAUSE AIN'T NO MAN
CUTTING NO SINGLE WOMAN'S GRASS

13:45.512 --> 13:47.413
UNLESS HE WANTS A LITTLE PIECE
OF SOMETHING.

13:47.413 --> 13:49.883
OH, BOY,
HUSH YOUR MOUTH, NOW.

13:49.883 --> 13:52.418
THAT MAN IS GRIEVING
AND GOING THROUGH.

13:52.418 --> 13:54.054
IT'S FINE.

13:55.421 --> 13:56.623
YEAH, WELL,
HE CUT IT WRONG.

13:56.623 --> 13:57.858
[ LAUGHS ]

13:57.858 --> 14:00.026
I TOLD HIM THAT, TOO.

14:00.026 --> 14:03.103
NOW, COME ON IN THE HOUSE.
LEAVE THIS GRASS ALONE.

14:03.103 --> 14:04.270
COME ON.

14:04.270 --> 14:07.273
MAN,
IT'S GOOD TO BE HOME.

14:07.273 --> 14:09.976
IT'S GOOD TO HAVE YOU HOME,
TOO.

14:09.976 --> 14:11.912
COME ON.

14:11.912 --> 14:13.947
MNH‐MNH.

14:13.947 --> 14:15.916
I WANT TO FEEL THE SUNSHINE
ON MY FACE FOR A MOMENT.

14:15.916 --> 14:17.918
[ DOG BARKS ]

14:17.918 --> 14:20.887
YOU WANT TO SIT OUT HERE
FOR A LITTLE WHILE?

14:23.924 --> 14:24.925
NO.

14:24.925 --> 14:27.093
[ LAUGHS ]

14:27.093 --> 14:29.262
I WANT TO STAND UP.

14:30.997 --> 14:33.233
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

14:33.233 --> 14:35.769
I WANT TO FEEL THE GRASS
UNDERNEATH MY FEET.

14:37.638 --> 14:38.705
COME ON, DO IT.

14:38.705 --> 14:39.740
WHAT?

14:39.740 --> 14:41.708
COME ON.
DO IT WITH ME.

14:41.708 --> 14:42.976
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

14:42.976 --> 14:44.344
BOY, THESE PEOPLE
GONNA THINK WE CRAZY.

14:44.344 --> 14:47.013
I DON'T CARE ABOUT THESE PEOPLE.
COME ON!

14:47.013 --> 14:48.348
KICK YOUR SHOES OFF.

14:48.348 --> 14:53.253
OH, BENJAMIN, BENJAMIN,
BENJAMIN, YOU KNOW I LOVE YOU.

14:53.253 --> 14:54.454
MM, MM, MM.

14:54.454 --> 14:55.488
DO YOU SEE?

14:57.223 --> 14:59.826
NOW WHAT WE DO?
[ LAUGHS ]

14:59.826 --> 15:01.434
ENJOY IT.

15:02.936 --> 15:05.572
WHEN'S THE LAST TIME
YOU DID SOMETHING LIKE THIS?

15:05.572 --> 15:06.840
OOH‐WEE.

15:06.840 --> 15:08.942
HMM?
I WAS A CHILD.

15:08.942 --> 15:11.978
NO, YOU WERE A CHILD.

15:11.978 --> 15:14.047
YOU WERE OUT HERE
WITH YOUR SISTER,

15:14.047 --> 15:16.382
AND Y'ALL WOULD BE PLAYING,
AND I'D BE ‐‐

15:16.382 --> 15:18.885
LORD.

15:18.885 --> 15:20.554
HOW DID CANDACE
TURN OUT SO BAD?

15:20.554 --> 15:22.623
DON'T EVEN START.

15:24.257 --> 15:26.660
BENNY,
I NEED TO FIND HER BABY.

15:27.694 --> 15:29.429
MOM, I'M SURE
THAT BABY'S FINE.

15:29.429 --> 15:31.431
YOU KNOW CANDACE.
SHE'S NOT GONNA HURT THAT BABY.

15:31.431 --> 15:34.901
I DON'T KNOW, BENNY. SOMETHING
JUST DON'T FEEL RIGHT ABOUT IT.

15:34.901 --> 15:36.469
STOP IT.

15:36.469 --> 15:38.672
YOU KNOW WHAT? I'M NOT GONNA
BOTHER YOU ABOUT THIS.

15:38.672 --> 15:41.174
YOU JUST GOT HOME.
[ LAUGHS ]

15:45.111 --> 15:47.213
WHAT?

15:47.213 --> 15:49.015
YOU KNOW
HOW MUCH I LOVE YOU?

15:51.351 --> 15:53.554
YEAH, BABY, I KNOW.

15:57.123 --> 15:58.759
MM.

15:58.759 --> 16:01.434
YOU KNOW
HOW MUCH I LOVE YOU?

16:01.434 --> 16:02.503
[ CRIES ]

16:02.503 --> 16:04.104
OOH, BENNY, DON'T CRY.

16:04.104 --> 16:06.540
YOU'RE GONNA MAKE ME CRY.
HMM.

16:10.276 --> 16:11.845
[ SNIFFLES ]

16:11.845 --> 16:13.346
IT WAS CRAZY IN THERE.

16:13.346 --> 16:14.447
YEAH.

16:17.718 --> 16:19.720
[ CRIES ]
I ALMOST DIED.

16:22.556 --> 16:25.959
BUT YOU DIDN'T, BABY.
YOU DIDN'T.

16:25.959 --> 16:29.229
PRAISE GOD YOU DIDN'T.

16:32.398 --> 16:34.801
Man:
HEY, WELCOME BACK, BENNY.

16:34.801 --> 16:36.302
HEY, APPRECIATE IT,
BRAH!

16:36.302 --> 16:37.804
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

16:37.804 --> 16:40.440
[ CHUCKLES ]
COME ON IN THIS HOUSE.

16:40.440 --> 16:43.844
PEOPLE STARTING TO LOOK AT US
LIKE WE DON'T OWN NO SHOES.

16:43.844 --> 16:45.378
[ LAUGHS ]

16:45.378 --> 16:47.047
OKAY.

16:47.047 --> 16:48.949
COME ON.

16:48.949 --> 16:52.318
YEAH, HE'S BACK!
[ LAUGHS ]

16:52.318 --> 16:53.319
COME ON.

16:53.319 --> 16:54.588
PUT YOUR SHOES BACK ON.

16:54.588 --> 16:56.256
[ LAUGHS ]

16:56.256 --> 16:58.224
UNH‐UNH NOW.
FEELS GOOD OFF.

16:58.224 --> 17:00.200
[ LAUGHS ]
WHOO!

17:03.737 --> 17:05.839
[ KEYS JINGLING ]

17:29.029 --> 17:30.230
HI.

17:30.230 --> 17:31.665
HEY.

17:31.665 --> 17:33.734
WHAT'S THE LATEST?
FILL ME IN.

17:33.734 --> 17:36.336
SO, I SPOKE TO MY CONTACT
DOWN AT THE D. A.'S OFFICE.

17:36.336 --> 17:37.403
YEAH?

17:37.403 --> 17:39.706
SAYS THEY SPOKE TO HANNA.

17:39.706 --> 17:42.242
SHE IS GONNA TESTIFY
THAT IT WAS WYATT.

17:44.244 --> 17:45.546
IS THAT RIGHT?

17:45.546 --> 17:46.913
YEAH.

17:46.913 --> 17:49.950
AND THEY'RE GONNA
REARREST WYATT.

17:49.950 --> 17:52.753
THEY'RE GONNA ARREST MY SON
AGAIN.

17:52.753 --> 17:54.487
YES.
GOD.

17:54.487 --> 17:56.557
THEY'RE BANKING
THE ENTIRE ARREST

17:56.557 --> 18:00.133
ON THE MOTHER'S
EYEWITNESS STATEMENT AND HANNA.

18:02.135 --> 18:03.403
OKAY.

18:06.573 --> 18:08.308
THANK YOU.

18:08.308 --> 18:10.744
ANYTHING ELSE?

18:14.548 --> 18:16.550
NO, OUR BUSINESS IS DONE,
BYRON.

18:19.052 --> 18:20.353
OKAY.

18:20.353 --> 18:21.888
HEY!

18:23.423 --> 18:25.992
I DON'T WANT YOU TO
TALK TO HANNA AGAIN.

18:28.094 --> 18:29.930
I'M SORRY?

18:29.930 --> 18:31.331
WHAT, DID I STUTTER?

18:31.331 --> 18:34.034
I DON'T WANT YOU TO
TALK TO HANNA AGAIN.

18:34.034 --> 18:35.502
OUR BUSINESS IS OVER.

18:35.502 --> 18:38.271
YOU HAVE NO REASON
TO BE TALKING TO HER.

18:38.271 --> 18:40.106
OKAY?

18:40.106 --> 18:41.942
UH...

18:44.545 --> 18:46.780
OH, WAIT JUST A MINUTE.

18:48.982 --> 18:50.183
YOU LIKE HER.

18:51.852 --> 18:54.054
[ SCOFFS ] NO.

18:54.054 --> 18:55.388
NO?
IT'S NOT LIKE THAT.

18:55.388 --> 18:57.658
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU TALKING TO?
YOU LIKE HER.

18:57.658 --> 18:59.860
IT'S ‐‐
SHE'S A NICE WOMAN, OKAY?

18:59.860 --> 19:01.868
OH, IS THAT RIGHT?
SHE'S A NICE WOMAN?

19:01.868 --> 19:03.136
YES, SHE IS.

19:03.136 --> 19:05.038
WELL, SHE'S BEEN REALLY NICE
TO ME, HASN'T SHE?

19:05.038 --> 19:06.673
LOOK, SHE DOESN'T HAVE MUCH.
SHE JUST NEEDS A FRIEND.

19:06.673 --> 19:08.842
AND YOU CAN'T BE THAT FRIEND,
BYRON.

19:08.842 --> 19:11.111
DO YOU REALIZE HOW MUCH
INFORMATION YOU HAVE ABOUT ME,

19:11.111 --> 19:13.580
INFORMATION THAT I DO NOT
WANT HER TO SEDUCE OUT OF YOU?

19:13.580 --> 19:15.381
DO YOU REALIZE THAT?
IT'S NOT LIKE THAT.

19:15.381 --> 19:18.218
NO, BUT IT SURE AS HELL
COULD BE LIKE THAT THAT QUICK.

19:18.218 --> 19:20.220
LET ME MAKE THIS CLEAR TO YOU,
OKAY?

19:20.220 --> 19:22.122
I HIRED YOU TO DO A JOB.
YOU DID IT.

19:22.122 --> 19:24.591
I PAID YOU TO DO THAT JOB.
IT'S OVER.

19:24.591 --> 19:27.227
YOU DON'T TALK TO
HANNA YOUNG AGAIN.

19:27.227 --> 19:29.395
YOU UNDERSTAND ME?

19:29.395 --> 19:31.431
[ WATER RUNNING ]

19:37.270 --> 19:39.339
[ DIALING ]

19:40.907 --> 19:43.610
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

19:43.610 --> 19:45.879
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

19:45.879 --> 19:48.114
THIS IS HER.

19:48.114 --> 19:49.783
ANSWER IT.

19:49.783 --> 19:51.885
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

19:51.885 --> 19:53.319
SPEAKER PHONE.

19:54.655 --> 19:56.623
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

19:56.623 --> 19:58.191
HEY, HANNA, WHAT'S UP?

19:58.191 --> 19:59.392
HEY, BYRON.

19:59.392 --> 20:01.401
LISTEN,
I HAVE TO MAKE THIS QUICK

20:01.401 --> 20:03.036
'CAUSE MY SON
IS IN THE SHOWER.

20:03.036 --> 20:04.204
WHAT IS IT?

20:04.204 --> 20:06.640
Listen, I'm throwing him
a surprise party tonight,

20:06.640 --> 20:08.709
and I was wondering
if you could make it.

20:08.709 --> 20:12.513
OH, ACTUALLY,
I HAVE A MEETING TONIGHT, HANNA.

20:12.513 --> 20:15.181
IS IT ABOUT WYATT CRYER?

20:15.181 --> 20:16.382
No, why?

20:16.382 --> 20:17.651
THE D. A. CALLED ME.

20:17.651 --> 20:20.220
They're sending a car for me
in the morning

20:20.220 --> 20:22.188
to make my statement.

20:22.188 --> 20:25.826
YOU SURE YOU WANT TO
GO THROUGH WITH THIS, HANNA?

20:27.360 --> 20:30.163
HE HAS TO PAY FOR THIS,
BYRON.

20:31.732 --> 20:33.667
I UNDERSTAND.

20:33.667 --> 20:35.736
Sorry you can't make it.

20:35.736 --> 20:37.470
YEAH.

20:37.470 --> 20:38.772
MR. CRYER?

20:38.772 --> 20:42.342
Uh, hey, hey, Hanna,
you there?

20:42.342 --> 20:43.910
Get back inside
this minute.

20:43.910 --> 20:45.078
HANNA?

20:48.314 --> 20:50.584
YEAH, YEAH, I'M HERE.

20:50.584 --> 20:53.286
UH, LOOK,
ON SECOND THOUGHT,

20:53.286 --> 20:55.689
MAYBE I WILL TRY
AND MAKE IT TO THE PARTY.

20:55.689 --> 20:56.790
WHAT TIME SHOULD I ‐‐

20:56.790 --> 20:58.458
NO.

20:58.458 --> 21:01.735
YOU'RE GONNA GO
TO YOUR MEETING.

21:01.735 --> 21:04.104
I'll call you later.

21:05.639 --> 21:06.940
ARE YOU SURE?

21:06.940 --> 21:09.142
YEAH.

21:10.143 --> 21:11.377
Okay.

21:11.377 --> 21:13.279
Um, tell him I ‐‐
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

21:17.450 --> 21:20.453
OH, THAT IS VERY TOUCHING,
BYRON.

21:20.453 --> 21:22.055
DID SHE HEAR HER?

21:23.524 --> 21:25.325
I THINK SO.

21:25.325 --> 21:27.861
DAMN IT!

21:37.971 --> 21:40.073
[ CRIES ]

21:51.317 --> 21:53.053
JEFFERY?

21:57.791 --> 22:00.333
WHY WERE YOU IN HIS ROOM?

22:05.739 --> 22:06.873
DAD ASKED ‐‐

22:06.873 --> 22:08.875
DON'T LIE TO ME.
DON'T LIE TO ME.

22:08.875 --> 22:11.545
I'M NOT LYING TO YOU, MOM.
I'M NOT.

22:11.545 --> 22:13.714
WHO DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE TALKING TO?

22:13.714 --> 22:17.117
[ SIGHS ]

22:17.117 --> 22:19.085
IS THIS
WHAT IT'S COME TO?

22:19.085 --> 22:21.688
YOU'RE ‐‐
YOU'RE DISREGARDING ME NOW?

22:21.688 --> 22:23.590
NO, MOM.

22:24.725 --> 22:26.760
THEN WHAT?

22:31.698 --> 22:32.766
WHAT?!

22:34.801 --> 22:37.370
I CALLED HIM LAST NIGHT.

22:38.572 --> 22:41.875
Y‐YOU DON'T KNOW HIM.

22:44.377 --> 22:46.412
I MET HIM ONCE.

22:46.412 --> 22:48.214
AND...

22:48.214 --> 22:49.550
[ SIGHS ]

22:49.550 --> 22:51.117
WHERE?

22:53.787 --> 22:55.288
AT A BAR.

22:57.524 --> 22:59.059
A BAR.

23:00.801 --> 23:03.937
UM...YEAH.

23:03.937 --> 23:09.075
ONE THAT ‐‐
THAT CANDACE TOOK ME TO.

23:09.075 --> 23:10.243
DAMN!

23:20.921 --> 23:23.089
WHAT KIND OF BAR, JEFFERY?

23:26.693 --> 23:28.762
GAY BAR.

23:31.898 --> 23:36.302
YOU MAKE ME WANT TO DRIVE
RIGHT OFF THIS BRIDGE.

23:36.302 --> 23:39.139
YOU'D BE DOING BOTH OF US
A FAVOR.

23:40.641 --> 23:42.776
[ SEAT BELT RELEASES ]

23:45.746 --> 23:48.414
BOY,
PUT YOUR SEAT BELT ON.

23:58.424 --> 24:00.393
[ SEAT BELT CLICKS ]

24:00.393 --> 24:02.002
I'M SORRY.

24:06.607 --> 24:10.644
HOW WAS YOUR DINNER
WITH MELISSA?

24:15.015 --> 24:16.983
GOOD.

24:18.719 --> 24:20.353
JUST GOOD?

24:23.289 --> 24:24.424
YEAH.

24:28.895 --> 24:30.296
WHAT DID YOU DO?

24:30.296 --> 24:31.331
[ SIGHS ]

24:36.537 --> 24:38.672
UM...

24:38.672 --> 24:39.940
WE ATE, AND ‐‐

24:39.940 --> 24:42.008
WHAT ELSE, JEFFERY?

24:50.917 --> 24:52.719
WHERE DID YOU GO?

24:52.719 --> 24:55.388
DID YOU ‐‐ DID YOU ‐‐
DID YOU WALK HER HOME?

24:55.388 --> 24:58.024
DID YOU KISS HER GOOD NIGHT?
WHAT HAPPENED?

24:58.024 --> 25:01.702
SHE STAYED AT MY HOUSE,
MOM.

25:06.172 --> 25:07.173
OKAY.

25:07.173 --> 25:09.876
YEAH, YEAH,
AND WE HAD SEX.

25:13.780 --> 25:15.348
O‐OKAY.

25:16.617 --> 25:18.318
I DID IT.

25:18.318 --> 25:21.087
I DID IT,
AND I HATED IT!

25:21.087 --> 25:24.658
ARE YOU HAPPY NOW?!

25:26.527 --> 25:27.728
ACTUALLY, YES, I AM.

25:27.728 --> 25:29.395
[ SCOFFS ]

25:31.765 --> 25:32.966
[ SIGHS ]

25:42.442 --> 25:48.048
HOW MANY, UH...GIRLS

25:48.048 --> 25:51.117
HAVE YOU BEEN WITH, SON?

25:54.320 --> 25:55.889
ONE.

26:05.506 --> 26:08.208
THIS WAS YOUR FIRST TIME.

26:10.276 --> 26:12.212
YEAH.

26:20.954 --> 26:22.556
[ CRIES ]

26:24.390 --> 26:26.392
[ SNIFFLES ]

26:26.392 --> 26:31.131
WELL, LOSING YOUR VIRGINITY
CAN BE...

26:31.131 --> 26:33.934
IT CAN BE COMPLICATED.

26:36.937 --> 26:40.641
I HATED MY FIRST TIME,
TOO.

26:40.641 --> 26:42.609
DO YOU KNOW WHAT I DID?

26:47.247 --> 26:50.116
I ASKED YOU A QUESTION,
JEFFERY.

26:54.655 --> 26:56.757
WHAT, MOM?

26:58.759 --> 26:59.860
I DID IT AGAIN.

26:59.860 --> 27:01.635
MOM, THAT'S NOT ME.

27:01.635 --> 27:04.705
AND THAT'S WHAT YOU WILL DO,
SON.

27:04.705 --> 27:07.440
YOU WILL DO IT AGAIN,

27:07.440 --> 27:12.378
AND YOU WILL DO IT AGAIN
AND AGAIN AND AGAIN AND AGAIN

27:12.378 --> 27:14.815
UNTIL IT BECOMES YOU!

27:20.821 --> 27:23.089
THAT'S WHAT YOU'LL DO.

27:25.859 --> 27:26.960
WHAT YOU'LL DO.

27:46.279 --> 27:49.683
Candace:
YES, SEND ME MY CONTACTS,
TRANSFER IT TO MY NEW PHONE.

27:49.683 --> 27:52.619
NO, I DID THAT.

27:52.619 --> 27:54.788
I‐I DID THAT, TOO.

27:54.788 --> 27:56.757
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]
[ SCOFFS ]

27:56.757 --> 27:58.992
BENNY.

27:58.992 --> 28:01.134
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

28:01.134 --> 28:02.202
HELLO?

28:02.202 --> 28:04.337
CANDACE. CANDACE,
WHERE YOU BEEN AT?

28:04.337 --> 28:06.039
YOU HAD ME WORRIED SICK
ABOUT YOU.

28:07.908 --> 28:09.142
BENNY?

28:09.142 --> 28:10.544
GIRL,
WHERE YOU BEEN AT?!

28:11.878 --> 28:13.146
OH, MY GOD.

28:13.146 --> 28:15.281
LOOK, I'M ALL RIGHT.
I'M ALL RIGHT.

28:17.684 --> 28:19.219
[ CRIES ] I ‐‐

28:19.219 --> 28:22.222
SHH, SHH, LISTEN, I KNOW YOU'RE
UPSET, OKAY, BUT I'M GOOD.

28:22.222 --> 28:24.190
I'M GOOD, ALL RIGHT?

28:24.190 --> 28:27.127
I'm sorry I had you
got so upset.

28:27.127 --> 28:28.762
I NEED TO SEE YOU.

28:28.762 --> 28:30.797
Well, come by the house.

28:30.797 --> 28:33.834
YOU KNOW SHE DOESN'T ‐‐
SHE DOESN'T WANT ME THERE.

28:33.834 --> 28:36.036
CANDACE,
COME BY THE HOUSE.

28:37.571 --> 28:40.306
OKAY.
OKAY, I'LL COME BY LATER.

28:40.306 --> 28:41.508
Okay.

28:41.508 --> 28:42.876
I LOVE YOU, BENNY.

28:42.876 --> 28:44.745
I LOVE YOU, BABY SIS.

28:44.745 --> 28:48.549
NO...DON'T HANG UP.

28:48.549 --> 28:50.283
[ CHUCKLES ] LISTEN,
MOMMY'S IN THE KITCHEN.

28:50.283 --> 28:52.052
I'M SURE SHE'S GONNA KNOW
WHO I'M TALKING TO,

28:52.052 --> 28:53.654
SO I'LL SEE YOU LATER ON
TONIGHT, OKAY?

28:54.921 --> 28:56.356
I LOVE YOU, BENNY.

28:56.356 --> 28:58.825
GOD, I LOVE YOU SO MUCH,
SWEETHEART.

29:01.301 --> 29:02.836
[ SNIFFLES ]

29:02.836 --> 29:03.937
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

29:05.171 --> 29:06.206
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

29:12.345 --> 29:15.348
[ INHALES, EXHALES ]

29:17.483 --> 29:19.119
MAMA.

29:19.119 --> 29:20.887
YEAH?

29:20.887 --> 29:23.189
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

29:23.189 --> 29:24.290
NOTHING.

29:24.290 --> 29:26.960
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
DON'T GET MAD AT ME.

29:26.960 --> 29:29.462
[ SIGHS ] WHAT IS IT?

29:29.462 --> 29:31.331
CANDACE COMING BY HERE
LATER ON TONIGHT.

29:31.331 --> 29:33.233
OH, BENNY.
LOOK, I DON'T WANT TO HEAR IT.

29:33.233 --> 29:35.836
[ SCOFFS ]

29:35.836 --> 29:36.903
OKAY.

29:36.903 --> 29:38.705
ALL RIGHT.

29:38.705 --> 29:41.842
WE GONNA SIT DOWN HERE
LIKE A NICE FAMILY TONIGHT.

29:41.842 --> 29:43.176
OKAY.

29:43.176 --> 29:45.178
ALL RIGHT.

29:45.178 --> 29:47.213
AND ANOTHER THING ‐‐
I'M THE MAN OF THIS HOUSE,

29:47.213 --> 29:49.149
AND THAT'S WHAT I SAY,
SO THAT'S WHAT I ‐‐

29:49.149 --> 29:50.316
THAT'S WHAT IT'S GONNA BE.

29:50.316 --> 29:51.618
[ CHUCKLES ]

29:51.618 --> 29:54.020
ALL RIGHT, MR. MAN OF THE HOUSE,
ASK HER TO BRING HER BABY.

29:54.020 --> 29:55.388
LISTEN, I'M NOT DOING THIS

29:55.388 --> 29:57.423
WITH NEITHER ONE OF Y'ALL TODAY,
OKAY?

29:57.423 --> 29:58.725
SHE'S COMING BY HERE,

29:58.725 --> 30:01.602
SO YOU'RE GONNA SEE HER,
AND YOU'RE GONNA BEHAVE.

30:01.602 --> 30:03.670
MM.

30:03.670 --> 30:05.872
I WILL.

30:05.872 --> 30:08.208
OH?

30:08.208 --> 30:09.743
I WILL.

30:09.743 --> 30:12.245
[ SCOFFS ]

30:13.479 --> 30:15.749
I WILL.

30:15.749 --> 30:16.950
FINE.

30:16.950 --> 30:18.151
FINE.

30:18.151 --> 30:21.387
GO PUT SOME CLOTHES ON.
[ LAUGHS ]

30:21.387 --> 30:23.389
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

30:26.326 --> 30:27.894
WHERE THE HELL DID HE GO,
ROSE?

30:27.894 --> 30:29.596
HE MUST HAVE SLIPPED OUT.

30:29.596 --> 30:31.164
I'M UNDER A LOT OF PRESSURE
HERE.

30:31.164 --> 30:33.834
YEAH, WHY CAN'T I
GIVE YOU ANOTHER GUY?

30:33.834 --> 30:35.135
NO, I WANT THIS GUY.

30:35.135 --> 30:37.303
I SELECTED THIS GUY
SPECIFICALLY.

30:37.303 --> 30:39.439
OKAY, OKAY.

30:39.439 --> 30:41.307
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND,
ROSE.

30:41.307 --> 30:43.710
I NEED THIS GUY,
AND I NEED HIM TODAY,

30:43.710 --> 30:45.846
OR THIS WHOLE THING
IS GOING TO FALL APART.

30:45.846 --> 30:48.649
YOU KNOW WHAT BOTHERS ME
IS THAT HE TRIED TO RUN FROM <i>US.</i>

30:48.649 --> 30:50.817
JUST FIND HIM, OKAY?

30:50.817 --> 30:53.253
MY BOYS
ARE DROPPING A DRAGNET.

30:53.253 --> 30:56.489
IF HE'S WITHIN SEVEN COUNTIES,
I'LL KNOW IT.

30:56.489 --> 30:59.392
OKAY, THAT'S ‐‐
ALL RIGHT, THAT'S GOOD.

30:59.392 --> 31:01.702
PLEASE, THANK YOU,
AND HURRY.

31:01.702 --> 31:05.005
OKAY, BUT YOU NEED TO
COME BY THE RESTAURANT.

31:05.005 --> 31:08.041
YOU KNOW I CAN'T DO THAT, ROSE.
I'VE EXPLAINED THAT BEFORE.

31:08.041 --> 31:09.142
I'LL CALL YOU LATER.

31:09.142 --> 31:11.377
Yeah,
not if I call you first.

31:11.377 --> 31:13.446
LET'S HOPE
THAT'S THE CASE.

31:13.446 --> 31:16.449
THAT MEANS YOU'RE GONNA BE
NEEDING ME FOR A CHANGE,

31:16.449 --> 31:17.818
AND I CAN COME TO YOU.

31:17.818 --> 31:19.052
[ SCOFFS ]

31:19.052 --> 31:21.321
I WON'T LET YOU DOWN, JIM.

31:21.321 --> 31:23.056
You never do, Rose.

31:23.056 --> 31:25.859
HEY, BY THE WAY, W‐WHATEVER
HAPPENED TO THAT GIRL?

31:25.859 --> 31:27.561
IS SHE STILL
BOTHERING YOU?

31:27.561 --> 31:29.863
NO, I HAVEN'T HEARD A WORD
FROM HER.

31:29.863 --> 31:32.666
[ SCOFFS ] YOU SHOULD HAVE
LET US TAKE HER OUT.

31:32.666 --> 31:34.267
NO, YOU DID A GREAT JOB.

31:34.267 --> 31:36.737
SHE LEARNED HER LESSON,
BELIEVE ME.

31:36.737 --> 31:39.172
OKAY, GOOD.

31:39.172 --> 31:42.743
I'LL CHECK IN WITH YOU
ABOUT NORM.

31:42.743 --> 31:45.011
YES, THANK YOU,
AND HURRY.

31:45.011 --> 31:47.247
PLEASE.

31:47.247 --> 31:48.649
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

31:54.287 --> 31:57.624
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

31:57.624 --> 31:59.192
<i>JUDGE JIM CRYER IS EXPECTED</i>

31:59.192 --> 32:01.968
<i>TO ANNOUNCE HIS CANDIDACY</i>
<i>FOR GOVERNOR TOMORROW.</i>

32:01.968 --> 32:04.137
<i>THE 8:00 A. M. CELEBRATION</i>
<i>WILL BE ATTENDED</i>

32:04.137 --> 32:05.939
<i>BY SEVERAL FORMER GOVERNORS.</i>

32:05.939 --> 32:07.273
<i>THERE'S EVEN A RUMOR</i>

32:07.273 --> 32:09.475
<i>THAT FORMER PRESIDENT WILHOUSE</i>
<i>WILL BE THERE.</i>

32:09.475 --> 32:11.411
<i>THE MAYOR AND GOVERNOR</i>
<i>ARE EXPECTED</i>

32:11.411 --> 32:13.980
<i>TO ATTEND THE RALLY</i>
<i>OUTSIDE CAMPAIGN HEADQUARTERS.</i>

32:13.980 --> 32:16.049
<i>THE EXCITEMENT IN THE AIR</i>
<i>FOR THE ANNOUNCEMENT</i>

32:16.049 --> 32:17.350
<i>IS UNBELIEVABLE.</i>

32:17.350 --> 32:19.385
<i>JIM CRYER IS MARRIED,</i>
<i>AS MOST PEOPLE KNOW,</i>

32:19.385 --> 32:21.622
TO HIS WIFE, KATHERYN.
WE NEED TO DO IT TONIGHT.

32:21.622 --> 32:24.390
YES, I'M SURE.

32:24.390 --> 32:27.193
I'VE NEVER BEEN
SO SURE.

32:27.193 --> 32:29.429
MY OTHER LINE IS RINGING.
I'LL CALL YOU BACK.

32:29.429 --> 32:31.431
<i>...WEALTHY BUSINESSMAN</i>
<i>AND POLITICIAN</i>

32:31.431 --> 32:33.499
<i>LEFT HIS FORTUNE AND FAME</i>
<i>TO KATHERYN.</i>

32:33.499 --> 32:34.500
HELLO?

32:34.500 --> 32:36.169
HI.

32:36.169 --> 32:37.203
Amanda?

32:37.203 --> 32:39.205
I'VE BEEN TRYING
TO CALL YOU.

32:39.205 --> 32:41.241
I JUST GOT A NEW PHONE.

32:41.241 --> 32:43.476
What happened
to the old one?

32:43.476 --> 32:45.546
PROBLEMS.

32:45.546 --> 32:47.681
OH, WELL,
YOU HAVEN'T TRIED TO CALL ME.

32:47.681 --> 32:51.652
NO, I'VE BEEN WORKING
ON SOMETHING.

32:51.652 --> 32:54.387
OH.
I WANT TO COME BACK.

32:54.387 --> 32:55.421
I know.

32:55.421 --> 32:57.658
BUT MY DAD
SAID I COULDN'T.

32:57.658 --> 32:59.860
I'M SURE OF IT.

32:59.860 --> 33:01.101
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:01.101 --> 33:03.003
WHY'D YOU THINK THAT?

33:03.003 --> 33:05.305
HE NEVER WANTED YOU
AROUND ME.

33:05.305 --> 33:06.507
He didn't?

33:06.507 --> 33:09.543
NO. YOU KNOW THAT.
HE OR YOUR MOM.

33:09.543 --> 33:12.879
OH, WELL, HE SAID
I COULDN'T TALK TO YOU, EITHER.

33:14.314 --> 33:16.249
DOES HE KNOW
THAT YOU ARE?

33:16.249 --> 33:17.751
No.

33:17.751 --> 33:19.152
OKAY.

33:21.622 --> 33:24.858
SO, I GUESS THAT LAWSUIT
BACKFIRED IN MY FACE, HUH?

33:24.858 --> 33:26.226
NOT QUITE.

33:26.226 --> 33:28.194
What do you mean?

33:28.194 --> 33:30.130
IT'S NOT OVER.

33:30.130 --> 33:32.966
I HAVE A PLAN, TOO.

33:32.966 --> 33:34.735
What's that?

33:34.735 --> 33:36.837
HAVE YOU SEEN QUINCY?

33:38.038 --> 33:39.372
WHO?

33:39.372 --> 33:41.074
QUINCY.

33:43.076 --> 33:44.077
HOW DO YOU KNOW ‐‐

33:44.077 --> 33:45.579
CUT IT OUT, CANDACE.

33:45.579 --> 33:48.381
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME
YOU HAD A BABY?

33:48.381 --> 33:50.416
WHAT?

33:50.416 --> 33:53.119
HE TOLD ME EVERYTHING.

33:54.721 --> 33:56.957
WHAT ELSE DID HE ‐‐
WHAT DID HE TELL YOU?

33:56.957 --> 33:59.159
That you were
the love of his life,

33:59.159 --> 34:00.827
THAT YOU HAD A BABY
TOGETHER,

34:00.827 --> 34:03.369
AND THAT HE WENT TO JAIL
FOR MURDER.

34:05.405 --> 34:06.406
YEAH?

34:06.406 --> 34:07.574
Yeah.

34:07.574 --> 34:09.475
Is it true?

34:09.475 --> 34:13.246
UH, YEAH,
HE'S THE FATHER OF MY CHILD.

34:13.246 --> 34:15.181
WHERE'S THE BABY?

34:15.181 --> 34:17.450
What else did he say?

34:17.450 --> 34:19.252
THAT HE WAS
LOOKING FOR YOU.

34:19.252 --> 34:20.987
YEAH?

34:22.422 --> 34:24.991
UM,
WHERE DID YOU SEE HIM?

34:24.991 --> 34:27.393
HE WAS AT THE APARTMENT.

34:29.495 --> 34:31.131
SO, HE WAS HERE?

34:31.131 --> 34:32.833
YEAH.

34:32.833 --> 34:35.468
OKAY.

34:35.468 --> 34:39.205
SO, ARE YOU
ATTRACTED TO HIM?

34:39.205 --> 34:40.206
NO, NOT AT ALL.

34:40.206 --> 34:42.108
D‐DID HE SAY
HE WAS COMING BACK HERE?

34:42.108 --> 34:44.711
NO, BUT I CAN CALL HIM
AND TELL HIM WHERE YOU ARE.

34:44.711 --> 34:47.047
NO, A‐AMANDA,
DON'T DO THAT.

34:47.047 --> 34:48.414
ARE YOU SURE?

34:48.414 --> 34:51.451
Yes, don't tell him
where I am.

34:51.451 --> 34:52.452
OKAY.

34:52.452 --> 34:55.155
UM ‐‐ WAIT.

34:55.155 --> 34:58.291
WHY ‐‐ WHY DO YOU
HAVE HIS NUMBER?

34:58.291 --> 35:02.202
HE GAVE ME HIS NUMBER SO IF
I SAW YOU, I COULD CALL HIM.

35:03.937 --> 35:05.672
OKAY.

35:05.672 --> 35:07.173
IS THAT SO?

35:07.173 --> 35:08.742
Yeah.

35:10.043 --> 35:12.312
BUT I ALSO THINK
THAT HE GAVE ME HIS NUMBER

35:12.312 --> 35:14.347
'CAUSE HE WAS FLIRTING
WITH ME.

35:14.347 --> 35:16.650
WAS HE?

35:16.650 --> 35:18.418
YEAH.

35:18.418 --> 35:20.621
WELL, YOU SHOULD
STAY AWAY FROM HIM.

35:20.621 --> 35:21.688
Why?

35:21.688 --> 35:22.856
HE'S DANGEROUS.

35:22.856 --> 35:23.890
I KNOW.

35:23.890 --> 35:26.326
HE TOLD ME ALL ABOUT
THE PEOPLE HE KILLED.

35:27.828 --> 35:28.862
DID HE?

35:28.862 --> 35:31.832
YEAH, AND HE SHOWED ME
HIS TATTOOS OF THEM.

35:31.832 --> 35:33.333
I WANT SOME.

35:33.333 --> 35:36.136
You want some what?

35:36.136 --> 35:39.305
TATTOOS
FOR MURDERING PEOPLE.

35:40.607 --> 35:42.743
AMANDA, ARE YOU OKAY?

35:42.743 --> 35:44.477
YEAH.

35:44.477 --> 35:46.880
ARE YOU SURE
THAT YOU DON'T LIKE HIM?

35:46.880 --> 35:50.283
NO, NOT AT ALL.
WHY ARE YOU ASKING?

35:50.283 --> 35:52.619
[ CHUCKLES ]
I THINK HE'S CUTE.

35:52.619 --> 35:53.854
Amanda.

35:53.854 --> 35:55.088
WHAT?

35:55.088 --> 35:57.457
HE IS DANGEROUS.

35:57.457 --> 35:59.259
I KNOW.
I LIKE DANGER.

35:59.259 --> 36:01.301
AMANDA, I'M SERIOUS.

36:01.301 --> 36:05.071
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
HOW BAD HE C‐CAN BE.

36:05.071 --> 36:07.508
YEAH, I GOT TO GO.
MY DAD'S CALLING ME.

36:07.508 --> 36:08.742
Amanda...

36:08.742 --> 36:10.877
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

36:14.080 --> 36:15.215
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

36:37.704 --> 36:40.006
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

36:49.115 --> 36:51.217
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

36:51.217 --> 36:53.353
[ TV PLAYING ]

36:53.353 --> 36:55.656
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

36:55.656 --> 36:57.057
AMANDA: Hello?

36:57.057 --> 36:58.058
YO.

36:58.058 --> 36:59.392
HI.

36:59.392 --> 37:01.701
Who this?

37:01.701 --> 37:03.469
AMANDA.

37:03.469 --> 37:05.805
WHAT UP, GIRL?

37:05.805 --> 37:06.806
How are you?

37:06.806 --> 37:09.308
I'M GOOD.
YO, YOU HEARD FROM CANDY?

37:09.308 --> 37:12.045
MAYBE.

37:12.045 --> 37:13.613
Don't play with me.

37:13.613 --> 37:14.648
WHAT?

37:14.648 --> 37:16.783
YOU HEARD FROM CANDY
OR NOT?

37:18.484 --> 37:21.454
I HAVE A QUESTION FOR YOU
FIRST.

37:21.454 --> 37:22.989
What?

37:22.989 --> 37:26.259
WHERE DO I GET
A DEATH TATTOO?

37:26.259 --> 37:27.493
WHAT?

37:27.493 --> 37:29.896
I WANT A TATTOO.

37:29.896 --> 37:32.365
DID YOU HEAR FROM CANDY?

37:33.834 --> 37:37.170
TAKE ME TO GET A TATTOO,
AND I'LL TELL YOU.

37:37.170 --> 37:39.139
A TATTOO?

37:39.139 --> 37:42.175
YEAH,
I WANT A DEATH TATTOO.

37:42.175 --> 37:44.678
YOU GOT TO KILL SOMEBODY
FOR THAT.

37:44.678 --> 37:46.312
I KNOW.

37:46.312 --> 37:49.249
I ALREADY HAVE THE NAMES.

37:51.585 --> 37:53.086
WHO ARE THEY?

37:54.555 --> 37:56.657
MY FAMILY.

37:56.657 --> 37:59.492
YOU C‐‐ YOU CRAZY, RIGHT?

37:59.492 --> 38:01.702
DON'T CALL ME CRAZY.

38:01.702 --> 38:05.772
ALL RIGHT, I KNOW WHERE
YOU CAN GET A TATTOO.

38:05.772 --> 38:07.908
OKAY.

38:07.908 --> 38:10.611
CAN YOU COME PICK ME UP?

38:10.611 --> 38:13.514
I DON'T GOT NO CAR.
YOU COME GET ME.

38:13.514 --> 38:16.416
THEY WON'T LET ME
HAVE MY KEYS.

38:16.416 --> 38:17.518
Who?

38:17.518 --> 38:18.785
MY PARENTS.

38:18.785 --> 38:21.154
YOU'RE NOT GONNA LET THAT
STOP YOU, ARE YOU?

38:21.154 --> 38:24.625
I'M IN PRISON HERE.

38:24.625 --> 38:27.027
GIRL, YOUR ASS DON'T KNOW
NOTHING ABOUT PRISON.

38:27.027 --> 38:29.830
TELL ME ABOUT IT.

38:29.830 --> 38:31.632
ALL RIGHT.

38:31.632 --> 38:34.034
I'MA FIND SOME WHEELS,
AND I'MA COME GET YOU.

38:34.034 --> 38:35.902
OKAY.

38:35.902 --> 38:37.571
What's your address?

38:37.571 --> 38:39.239
I'LL TEXT IT TO YOU.

38:39.239 --> 38:41.975
YEAH, DO THAT.

38:41.975 --> 38:44.110
OKAY, BYE.

38:46.580 --> 38:48.582
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

38:48.582 --> 38:51.051
THIS CHICK CRAZY.

38:51.051 --> 38:53.053
[ TV PLAYING ]

38:53.053 --> 38:55.288
[ SIGHS ]

39:08.408 --> 39:09.743
YOU ARE CRAZY.

39:09.743 --> 39:10.911
I'M SORRY.
Jim: WHERE THE HELL IS HE?

39:10.911 --> 39:12.212
[ SIGHS ]

39:12.212 --> 39:13.647
HUH?

39:13.647 --> 39:14.981
HE WAS TRYING TO
LEAVE THE STATE,

39:14.981 --> 39:16.449
AS IF I DON'T
HAVE PEOPLE EVERYWHERE.

39:16.449 --> 39:18.051
YOU DON'T GET IT,
DO YOU, NORM?

39:18.051 --> 39:19.052
NO, HE DOESN'T.

39:19.052 --> 39:20.587
YOU CAN'T
GET OUT OF THE THING.

39:20.587 --> 39:22.322
ONCE YOU'RE IN IT,
YOU ARE IN IT.

39:22.322 --> 39:24.057
YOU HAVE NO CHOICE
IN THE MATTER.

39:24.057 --> 39:25.058
LOOK AT THIS.

39:25.058 --> 39:26.893
THIS IS YOUR DAUGHTER,
RIGHT?

39:26.893 --> 39:28.294
YOUR MOTHER?
LOOK AT IT.

39:28.294 --> 39:31.064
MY GUYS ARE RIGHT OUTSIDE
THEIR HOUSE RIGHT THIS MINUTE.

39:31.064 --> 39:34.801
ALL I HAVE TO DO IS SAY, "GO,"
AND THEY'RE DEAD.

39:34.801 --> 39:36.436
HE'S NOT PLAYING AROUND.

39:36.436 --> 39:38.539
DO I LOOK LIKE I'M PLAYING
AROUND TO YOU? HUH?

39:38.539 --> 39:41.708
OKAY, OKAY, I‐I'LL DO IT,
OKAY? OKAY?

39:41.708 --> 39:43.544
YOU'LL DO IT.
YOU'LL DO IT RIGHT DAMN NOW.

39:43.544 --> 39:45.445
OKAY.
COME GET HIM, BOYS!

39:45.445 --> 39:47.480
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

39:47.480 --> 39:49.182
GO ON!

39:49.182 --> 39:50.951
WE'LL DRIVE HIM OVER.

39:50.951 --> 39:52.318
[ CRIES ]

39:52.318 --> 39:53.620
THANK YOU.

39:53.620 --> 39:55.889
I TOLD YOU
I'D COME THROUGH.

39:55.889 --> 39:57.858
YEAH, YOU DID.

40:06.840 --> 40:09.009
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

40:14.180 --> 40:15.415
HI, AMANDA.

40:15.415 --> 40:16.416
WHAT?

40:16.416 --> 40:18.451
I DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING.

40:18.451 --> 40:21.555
GOOD. THEN DON'T.

40:21.555 --> 40:23.624
OKAY.

40:23.624 --> 40:25.859
YOU GOING SOMEWHERE?

40:26.927 --> 40:28.061
NO.

40:28.061 --> 40:29.963
THEN WHY DO YOU
KEEP LOOKING OUT THE WINDOW?

40:29.963 --> 40:31.932
BECAUSE I WANT TO.

40:34.868 --> 40:37.470
[ SPEAKS SPANISH ] WOW.

40:37.470 --> 40:40.106
[ SILVERWARE CLATTERS ]

40:40.106 --> 40:42.543
[ BRAKES SQUEAL ]

40:54.755 --> 40:56.222
[ CAR DOOR SHUTS ]

41:08.474 --> 41:10.844
COME ON, LET'S GO!

41:15.381 --> 41:16.617
[ CAR DOOR SHUTS ]
DRIVE!

41:16.617 --> 41:18.118
AMANDA?
DRIVE, GO!

41:18.118 --> 41:19.620
AMANDA!

41:23.089 --> 41:25.291
[ SPEAKS SPANISH ]

41:30.897 --> 41:32.999
David: NEXT ON
"THE HAVES AND THE HAVE NOTS"...

41:32.999 --> 41:34.000
HI.

41:34.000 --> 41:35.335
SUCH AN HONOR
TO MEET YOU.

41:35.335 --> 41:38.004
SO YOU'RE INTO OLDER MEN?
MOM! AMANDA'S GONE.

41:38.004 --> 41:40.173
I'M NOT ABOUT TO LET HIM COME
IN HERE AND HURT WHAT I LOVE.

41:40.173 --> 41:41.808
NO, YOU'RE NOT GOING NOWHERE.
JUST STOP IT!

41:41.808 --> 41:44.044
COMING OUT OF MY HOTEL ROOM
WITH MAGGIE.

41:44.044 --> 41:45.879
ARE YOU SLEEPING WITH
OUR CAMPAIGN MANAGER?

41:45.879 --> 41:48.114
SHE ASKED HOW THE DATE WAS AND
WHEN WE WERE GOING OUT AGAIN.

41:48.114 --> 41:49.115
W‐WHAT DID YOU SAY?

41:49.115 --> 41:50.551
I DIDN'T MENTION THE SEX,
OF COURSE.

41:50.551 --> 41:52.085
HANNA HAS A MEETING
IN THE MORNING WITH THE D. A.

41:52.085 --> 41:53.754
SHE'S GONNA GIVE HER
HER SWORN STATEMENT.

41:53.754 --> 41:55.055
SHE IS SURE
THAT IT WAS WYATT.

41:55.055 --> 41:56.723
THE POLICE ARE DOWNSTAIRS.
WHAT?

41:56.723 --> 41:57.858
YOU DON'T GIVE UP, DO YOU?

41:57.858 --> 41:59.860
NO, I DON'T.
HMM.
